<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<aiml version="2.0">
	<topic name="Networking">
    <category>
        <pattern>TELL ME MORE</pattern>
        <template>
            Networking connects our technology together this includes computers
            that are in the same building and computers on different continents. 
            Without the study and implementation of networking the internet 
            would not be what it is today. 
            Within the Networking field there are many careers to pursue. 
            Well-known professions include Network Architects and 
            Network Administrators. Which career would you like to know more about?
        </template>
    </category>
	<category>
	    <pattern>NETWORK ADMINISTRATOR</pattern>
	    <template>
	        Network Administrators setup, maintain and upgrade a companies networks
	        (WAN, LAN). In addition to maintining networks Network Administrators also
	        work to ensure the security of the network and upkeep of the computer
	        systems on the network.
	    </template>
    </category>
    <category>
        <pattern>ADMIN</pattern>
        <template><srai>NETWORK ADMINISTRATOR</srai></template>
    </category>
    <category>
	    <pattern>HOW MUCH DO NETWORK ADMINISTRATORS MAKE</pattern>
	    <template>
	        Network Administrators Median Pay:
	        $83,510 per year
	        
	        Source: ("Network and Computer Systems Administrators," 2020)
	    </template>
    </category>
    <category>
	    <pattern>WHAT SKILLS DO NETWORK ADMINISTRATORS NEED</pattern>
	    <template>
	        Network Administrators need to possess knowledge of 
	        computer systems and computer security in addition to networking
	        knowledge. Oftentimes network admins
	        work with systems by scripting languages. Certifications in
	        Microsoft and Cisco are also needed.
	    </template>
    </category>
	<category>
	    <pattern>NETWORK ARCHITECT</pattern>
	    <template>
	        According to the BLS, "computer network architects...
            Create plans and layouts for data communication networks
            Present plans to management and explain why they are in the 
            organizationâ€™s best interest to pursue them"
            and "Network architects also predict future network needs by analyzing
            current data traffic and estimating how growth will affect the network"
            ("Network and Computer Systems Administrators," 2020)."
	    </template>
	</category>
	<category>
        <pattern>ARCHITECT</pattern>
        <template><srai>NETWORK ARCHITECT</srai></template>
    </category>
	<category>
    	<pattern>HOW MUCH DO NETWORK ARCHITECTS MAKE</pattern>
	    <template>
	        Network Architect Median Pay:
	        $112,690 per year
	        
	        Source: ("Computer Network Architects," 2020)
	    </template>
    </category>
    <category>
	    <pattern>WHAT SKILLS DO NETWORK ARCHITECTS NEED</pattern>
	    <template>
	        According to the BLS, Network Architects need to posses the skills
	        of a Network Admin (listed below) and they also must have skills in Business
	        Administration due to the need for them to work with higher management
	        to make large scale decisions about a company's network design and
	        the integration of new technology ("Computer Network Architects," 2020).
	        
	        Network Admin Skills:
	        Network Admins need to possess knowledge of 
	        computer systems and computer security in addition to networking
	        knowledge. Oftentimes network admins
	        work with systems by scripting languages. Certifications in
	        Microsoft and Cisco are also needed.
	    </template>
	</category>
